animal.description:
Oh-oh-oh, get in the action
Feel the attraction!

Little miss Shania Twain says she will be singing a happy tune and dancing a happy dance if a wonderful Colorado family brings her home to love.

Sweet sweet Miss Shania is a three month old, Australian Sheppard mix puppy that just recently arrived in Colorful Colorado. So thrilled she was to have arrived in Colorado, she began running zoomies in the yard the moment her paws hit the grass.

Shania has been sleeping in a large cozy crate near her foster mama. Shania is just as excited for bedtime as her foster mama and happily runs ahead and into her crate at bedtime. Shania not only knows her routine, she also knows her foster mamas routine. As soon as Shania sees foster mama put on hand lotion, she knows the next step is to trot off to bed and she runs along ahead and into her crate. Shana likes to adjust her bedding of towels and blankets to make herself a little nest. Shania makes it the whole night, about 8 hours, before needing to go outside. Her first order of business when getting up in the morning is running down two flights of stairs and out to the yard to take care of her morning toiletries.

Shania has worked hard on house training and rarely has an accident. Accidents primarily occur because foster mama failed to notice her need or get the door open fast enough in the morning. Shania is even good at sitting by the door to alert her foster mama that she needs to go out. She may also whimper softly. Shanias foster mama has learned to trust Shanias communication. Foster mama also takes her out often just to reinforce her good behavior and give her ample opportunities to take care of business.

Shania loves to play and be around her people that she has bonded with. However, Shania is shy at first with new people and dogs. At first, Shania got a little spooked by unfamiliar noises, but she is feeling more confident and even starting to run closer to those folks and dogs that wish to greet her at the fence. Shania has made a couple of doggie friends at the fence and seems only to want to play.

Shania is a high energy puppy that desires attention and playtime. We have been taking a short walk every day and she is adjusting to the new activity. Some days go better than others and she may be willing to venture a little further on each walk. Other days she would prefer to turn back toward home. Foster mama is puzzled at times because Shania gets so excited when the leash comes out but then doesnt want to walk. We are working on this skill and trying to determine what triggers her fear of going out. Shania and foster mama play catch with soft toys and this girl can catch! Perhaps a future frisbee dog in the making?

Shania knows the sit command and learned very quickly. She has even been working on sit, stay, come, and doing well. However, she needs special attention to learning that feet and toes, fingers, and clothes are not appropriate chew toys. That behavior is still a work in progress.

Miss Shania has beautiful green eyes and a fine white fur coat with brown spots. She has the cutest brown patch of fur that highlights her bright green eye and another that surrounds her cute little nose.

Can you feel it?
Come, come, come on, baby!
I feel like I could be your happy puppy!

*Homeownership required!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Isabella is a female breeder release Yorkie. She has a sweet personality and loves to cuddle with her human. She gets along with both male and female humans, dogs and cats. She is currently learning what it means to live in a home and use a potty pad and go outside. Leash- what's that? She does resource guard. Isabella loves to play with her stuffed toys so make sure she's got an assortment to choose from. Isabella is timid and likes to make the first move, so take it slow when getting acquainted.

The suggested adoption donation for Isabella is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the animalss foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each pet, based on the pets needs. If you and the pet are not a good match, we will help you select another, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

Interested in saving more lives? Foster a dog today! Learn more, see our list of dogs needing foster, and apply, https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster-a-city-dog.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster-based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. animal.description:
Dipstick is a fun, extremely goofy, extremely affectionate lover boy! 

And yes, he is cross-eyed! but it does not slow him down a bit, and really just adds to his incredibly enduring and lovable personality! He has a great attitude, and brings joy to everyone that crosses his path. 

He LOVES people and would do anything for a home where he could be someone's everyday side-kick! 

He is house trained, crate trained, and is working on his basic-advanced obedience.

He is currently in a foster home with his trainer @dogtrainerari and she is working him through his training program with @woofgangrehab and @shadesofbludogtraining.

He is doing extremely well will his foster fur-brother @artook9gsd and we believe he will do great with another dog to share a home with but he will have to meet any new siblings before adoption to ensure a good match. 

We pulled this adorable guy from the humane society where he had previously been rather unlucky. He has been returned to the shelter by multiple families, all of whom were either moving, not ready for a dog, and at one point he was left at a day care and the owner did not return for him. 

Because he has been moved around so much we will be very selective with his new forever home to ensure that he never have to go through the stress of being abandoned again.

Knowing all this, you can see that Dipstick is a very special boy, even after all of the neglect this pup has faced, he still has such a positive outlook on life, and is happy to be around anyone and go anywhere with an over-sized smile on his face! 

Dipstick is currently available for meet and greets and adoption but will only move into his forever home when his training is complete! 


Please view information about our rescue and mission on at following link before applying:

https://shadesofbludogtraining.com/rescue/woof-gang-rehab-rescue/



To apply for your new best friend, please fill out our online application! 

https://shadesofbludogtraining.com/rescue/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Hello there! My name is Gertie! I am part Border Collie and part Lab; which makes me a Borador! I am about 10 months old and currently weigh 51 lbs. I could use a few groceries though, as I am rather skinny. My foster parents think I will probably be about 65 lbs once I'm done growing and at a healthy weight. I have been with my foster family since January 24th and have had no accidents in the house and sleep quietly through the night in my kennel. I am very gentle and don't jump up on people. I am currently an only dog in my foster home, but am friendly with other dogs I've met at the rescue and on walks. I'm working on not barking at dogs I see while I'm on walks, but it's just because I'm so excited and want to go play with them. I'm also working on not whining when we walk by people, which is me just being upset they didn't come pet me. I sit for my food and am very smart so I should pick up new commands quickly. I enjoy my squeaky toys, chewing on bones, playing in snow, and cuddling with my foster parents. I am medium energy and match the energy of my foster parents. I am calm in the house, but am very active outside. I am not good with cats. I am a sweet girl looking for my furever home!

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 

Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you, please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

Hey there! My name is Buster and in a 42 lb, boxer/bull terrier mix and I’m about 9 months old. I’m the opposite of shy and I jump right into whatever we’re doing! I love chasing toys and playing with my foster sister but I also love to snuggle on the couch. If you’re not giving me enough attention I’ll nudge your hand onto my head for some extra pets. I take directions well and I’m learning fast. I sleep through the night and I do so in my crate without making a peep! I walk well on a leash without pulling but could use some training on walk etiquette unless you don’t mind my zig zagging (there’s just so many smells!) I don’t make very much noise but I’m good at letting you know what I want! I also do incredibly well on car rides but you should keep me in the back seat or I’ll try to crawl in your lap for cuddles. Contact Lucky Mutts to let them know you’d like to meet me today!

animal.description:
MEET GILLY!!

THIS DOG IS SLATED FOR EUTHANASIA by the County Shelter-- NEEDS IMMEDIATE FOSTER/ADOPTER.

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in it's possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4526063.

One of the saddest reasons a dog can be E-listed is because they are mentally breaking down in their kennel. This is what's happened to me. I am really struggling and it is inhumane to keep me here in this condition....Can someone save my life?

I am a young 2 year old pup looking for a foster or my furever home. Aren't I a handsome boy? My bio says I need to be the only dog. My first day in the play yard I growled at another dog, the next day I tolerated some dogs and allowed sniffing. So maybe I'm just dog selective? If you are interested in me and currently have dogs, bring them down so I can meet them! I'm very friendly with all people, I just need to get out of this shelter, it's not the place for me! I pull moderately hard on my leash and I bite it sometimes because I'm so excited, I will need a patient owner who will work on my training. I jump and get excited to see people, so it's best I don't go to a home with young children. It is possible some of these behaviors subside outside of the stressful shelter environment. Do you have room in your home for me?

To meet me, please call 480 331 4188 or message us here. If you have a dog you need to bring down for a dog intro. Dog Savers has got over 230 E-listed dogs in the last year out of the shelter alive! A small percent of the donations go to our operating costs to help these dogs get out alive. Lets keep working together to save lives!!

My ID is #A4526063...you'll need that if you want to save me. I am located in Phoenix Az.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Pico de la Poco! What can we say about this tiny gent other then he is too cute! Pico is about 4 years old and weighs 5 pounds. He is a fun little mix - our best guess is yorkie and terrier or chihuahua but there is probably all 3 or more in there. He has a long scruffy coat that can get out of control if not kept up on.

Pico is normally a little couch potato! He likes to be in his crate, all snuggled up with another little dog. He is happy just lounging around all day. He is normally a quiet boy but if there is any fun going on he becomes Sherriff Pico and wants to end it. There is no rough housing around him! He is working on his housetraining skills but will need more work in his new home so please be patient with him. His foster mom started working with him on the leash but he prefers the freedom of his fully fenced yard! Pico is good with other dogs and would like one in his new home. He sometimes barks at cats but it doesn't go further than that. He has not been tested with kids so at this point, he should be around kids 13+. Pico was initially very scared for his foster mom and didn't want to be picked up. After lots of work, Pico is ready to be picked up and will roll over for a belly rub. He may regress a bit in a new home with new people but once he feels secure, he will come around. Pico is a gentle little boy who's life was turned upside down when his family gave him up. All he wants is a loving home again!

Pico is neutered, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and tested neg. for heartworm. He has also been groomed recently! His adoption fee is $400

For my Petfinder.com friends, please contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information. My ID number is 336158

I am available for adoption; however due to my breed my adoption will have to be facilitated through a rescue organization. Please see the front desk staff or contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information.

Meet Anna! What's not to love about this velvety hippo??? Anna is simply the cutest girl, with the cutest wiggle! Anna is a happy lady, who is excited to be with and near people! She looks forward to going for walks and really enjoys play time. Anna came to the Shelter after being found running the streets, all by her self! Thankfully, her disposition is one of an elated girl. She deserves to be in a loving home where she is well tended to and cared for !

The following descriptions describe behaviors that were observed during testing and/or veterinary examination: Evaluated for temperament with 336753 (female), and 336619 (male). She was very vocal, but there were no red flags as far as posturing. Do recommend slow introductions to other dogs because of her exuberant voice 1/20/2021

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

animal.description:
Meet Roxie, a 5 year old  Retriever/hound/terrier mix.  She weighs about  55 lbs.   and is blind and diabetic.   Roxie was relinquished to the shelter due to her medical needs.  She is a sweet dog and has been and absolute champ about taken her medications and daily insulin injections. Please don’t let this  frighten or deter you from wanting to meet her.    PWD will help continue to assist her adoptive family  with her medical needs if needed.   

Roxie was fostered by an incredible person before being transported to us and  she has a lot of great things to say about this girl:

"Roxie is a sweet girl that absolutely loves people. She affectionately got the nickname "Potato" as she is a couch potato at heart but does enjoy going for walks and being outdoors. Her absolute favorite place to be though is in your lap. The few times she was around my 2-year-old nephew she was very gentle, and when he realized she couldn't find the ball as easily as our other dogs he would put it right in front of her and she would gently take it from him.   She is great with other animals as well. She enjoyed the quiet company of my 4 cats and would occasionally be found cuddling with them in bed. She enjoyed being around my dogs as well and would play on days she was feeling spunky but otherwise just enjoyed their company."

 
Please consider Roxie,  she would be a great companion and friend.

From the mean streets of San Francisco to the safety of Muttville, this little chihuahua mix comes with a "little big man" outlook on life. Quigley seems to have come from a tough life and looks forward to a forever home with a family who will love and accept him for all his quirks and complexities. 

Quigley is a bit of a lone wolf and is happiest doing his own thing. He likes to have his head and back scratched as long as it on his terms. He's a good eater and is very good about gently taking snacks from those he knows/trusts. 

Here is what his foster has to say:

Quigley's favorite thing to do is to lie out in the sun with occasional breaks inside for water and a cool-down. Quigley likes short walks but does tire after 15-20 minutes. He loves riding in a stroller where he can observe other dogs and people rather than encounter them.

We're working on his house training and he's made great strides! He understands potty pads and although has been wearing a belly band, he's been fine during the day with no accidents! He's happiest in the morning and has even been known to "play a game of hide and seek up and down the hall. In the evening, after dinner and a walk, Quigs wants to get in his bed and stay there uninterrupted until morning. 

Though he can manage the two steps at his foster home, he'd probably be happiest in a single story home/apartment. Quigley is best suited for a quiet and mature household. He will definitely do best with a family that has had experience with fearful dogs, understanding that patience and love will help Quigley bloom!

Quigley is a super cute little guy who is fairly independent. He enjoys being near his people and other dogs, but also likes his space. His favorite activity is going out for his walks as he loves a good sniffari! He can walk happily for about 15 minutes. After that he won't complain about staying outside, but sitting in a stroller. 

Our guess is that Quigley hasn't had the best past sadly. One vet said "he's been in a lot of pain for a very long time" - but we are helping to change that! He's had a dental, had an infected eye removed, and even had a little toe fixe. It takes him a while to warm up to people and trust them. He is not super snuggly and doesn't want to be fussed over, however he loves to know you are there and will sit in his own bed in the same room with you. He sometimes will even sit next to you on the sofa, but he's not a lap dog. 

He is looking for a very special person who understands his independence and is looking for a companion that is not needy. Quigley deserves just as much love and compassion as any other dog and we cannot wait for him to find his person. Are you that person who just wants to help a dog in need and not ask anything in return? If so then Quigley is your guy. His fans at Muttville can see the shining light behind that eye and really want to help him find a home that is going to understand his needs and help him to trust that humans aren't as terrible as he once knew them to be...

Quigley's Adoption fee is being sponsored by The Farmer's Dog!

She is looking for a patient, dog experienced owner that currently has another large dog. She looks to the other dog for her confidence. Sally also needs a secured fenced in yard. Please do not apply if you do not meet the needs of this dog as the application will not be considered.

animal.description:
READ BELOW BEFORE CONTINUING

"Shirley Temple”
1.5 Yrs Old
Female 
Carin / Brussels Griffon Mix
House & Crate training in progress
Other dog friendly 

**NOTE: SHIRLEY WILL NEED A VERY SPECIAL HOME.  SHE WILL BITE/SNAP IF BEING HANDLED, PICKED UP, ETC. UNTIL SHE COMPLETELY TRUSTS YOU**

IF YOU JUST WANT A COMPANION AND LOVE A CHALLENGE THEN SHES YOUR GIRL

IF YOU WANT A LAP DOG CUDDLE BUDDY SHE IS NOT YOUR GIRL UNTIL SHE COMPLETE TRUSTS YOU WHICH COULD BE MONTHS DOWN THE ROAD

Shirley Temple needs a home where she will be given time to adjust due to her trust issues. She needs an adopter that is dog savvy and is able to handle her spiciness. When she comes out of her shell she is like The Good Ship Lollipop taking off to candy land. She has a bubbly personality that will put a smile on your face. This goofy and silly girl will keep you on your dance toes so an active lifestyle would be ideal. She would prefer a fenced yard so she can work on her dance skills and get her zoomies out. She is still working on her potty skills and prefers not to be in a crate.

She is sweet in her own right and likes to be petted on her terms.

** A HOME WITH A FENCED  YARD IS A MUST **


Adoption fee is $300 with approved adoption application which includes age appropriate shots, rabies, spay/neuter, micro chip, heart worm test (treated if positive) started on monthly prevention if negative. Dental if needed as well as any other medical necessities. Comes with goody bag of toys, treats, collar, leash, etc. Also comes with 1 month (30 days) of free doggie health insurance.

NOTE: We do not adopt outside of a 75 mile radius of our location
NOTE: This dog would not be suited for Town home, Condo or Apartment living.
NOTE: We do not adopt to families with children under the age of 7

animal.description:
This is what my foster parent said about me:

I would describe him as energetic, curious, easygoing, and happy.

Dolby would do best in a home with energetic people and a family who will give him loads of attention!

His energy level is Medium.

He is both leash trained and house trained.

He paws at the door when he needs to go out.

He does not like his crate but calms down after 15 or so minutes of being in the crate.

When he's alone we put him in his crate, again he whines for a while but he calms down.

Does not chew on anything other than his toys!

He sleeps in his crate half the time, and one of our beds the other half.

He has not met cats, but he's met dogs and thinks everyone is his best friend!

He loves strangers, greets them and shows them love.

When he meets strangers on his leash he pulls towards them but this is just cause he gets excited.

Hasn't met younger kids before but I am confident he would do very well with kids! He does not care what you do to him; he has so much trust in us.

Dolby would do best in a home with lots going on and many friends Primary Color: Brindle Secondary Color: White Weight: 41lbs Age: 1yrs 6mths 3wks Animal has been Neutered

My name is Hops. I'm a 2 year old Pit Bull mix. Active people need active pets (and vice versa)! If you have a physically active lifestyle, I am the perfect dog for you. I have loads of energy and am looking for a family that can use that energy in positive ways. I'll do best in a home that has plenty of room and a fenced yard. Daily exercise and obedience training will help make me a happy, well-mannered dog. Please take me to the park, on hikes, and on morning jogs with you!

From: Animal Control
Weight: 43 lbs
Exercise: High Energy
Large/Small dogs: I like to play with other dogs. I do have lots of energy and may be too much for older dogs. You can always bring in your dog(s) to visit with me.
Children: I have lots of energy and forget my manners sometimes. Please bring the whole family in to make sure I'm the right fit for you.
Cats/other small animals: Unknown, ask an adoption counselor about doing a cat test with me.

Requirements: Must go to a home with adults only. Best suited to a home without children as he can be quite bashful.

Requirements: Will need consistent obedience training, appropriate socialization, extra enrichment, and adequate exercise.

Sex: Male
 
Age: Adult- 1 year old

Energy Level: High

Strength Level: High

Walks Best With: Freedom Harness

Working On: General manners & not jumping up on people.

Intake Reason: Stray

More About this Pet: I'm a big blockhead boy who loves to play with toys and go for long walks! Once I get to know you, I give the best hugs and slobbery kisses. I had a difficult past, so sometimes meeting new people and dogs can make me a little nervous and overwhelmed.

If you want to adopt me, you'll have to come meet me at the shelter first and bring your dog (if you have one) to see if we like each other. Despite being over 80 pounds, I'm just a big, gentle giant and couch potato. I am a dream to walk on leash and I don't pull at all. I know how to stick right by your side. I promise to be your loyal best friend for life if you give me a chance. Our behavior team will be happy to tell you all about me. I can't wait to get out of here and go to my forever home!

If you are interested in learning more about adopting this pet, click the [Adopt me] button to apply. 
Find a link to adopt this pet on our website: https://www.mdspca.org/humane-care/adopt/

animal.description:
WATCH! THE VIDEO OF ZINNIA'S NEW BEGINING! 
*********************************************
THE TUCSON COMMUNITY RALLIED TOGETHER TO SAVE THIS YOUNG MOTHER THAT WAS DUMPED IN THE DESERT!!!
 Yes!!!! Right before Christmas, lactating Zinnia was dumped in the desert by the side of the road where she stayed for days waiting for that familiar car that Never returned! A DEDICATED group of women tried desperately to gain her trust but she only wanted that car!
After a week she began to roam through the desert with her Rescue Angels hot on her trail..sightings were posted on NEXT-DOOR and  at all hours of the day and night these gals never gave up! They borrowed a professional trap that they constantly moved when she did with life saving food and water! After 3 long weeks....it was Zinnia's Lucky Day thanks to some smelly cat food! The Rescue Angels took her to the HSSAZ where the veterinarians removed cactus from her mouth and body and the Fabulous, Rachel Molyneux from Sol Dog Lodge & Training Center picked her up yesterday and Zinnia's New Life Begins!; Zinnia has had a rough 2 months To Say The Least....and will be in board & train at Sol Dog until she is ready for adoption!!!!
* If you would like to donate to Zinnia's recovery you can do so directly at: https://soldoglodge.com/donate/ and specify to Zinnia's Care  Special Thanks to Roxanne Washington for
   NEVER GIVING UP ON ZINNIA!

        IT TAKES A VILLAGE!!!

STAY TUNED FOR PHOTOS AND UPDATES!
ZINNIA WILL BE AVAILABLE SOON FOR ADOPTION AT SMILINGDOGRESCUE.COM

animal.description:
Time to get serious about spending forever with me! My name is Mega Man! I am a dashing, 1 year old, 20lb., Hound mix guy! I am working on beefing up to the 40lb. dog I should be! I am sweet as pie. I am good with other dogs and will need a fenced in yard. I have been working hard to master house training but am amazing when crated! Time to get serious about us and fill out that application!


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.KIPPIE MAKES YOU SMILE. He's just that kind of Cocker Spaniel. He is such a happy boy and his tail never stops wagging. He is very energetic for a 10 year-old. His love for food has made him on the chubby side at 33 pounds, so he is on a diet plan. He loves food so much that he will bark for what you have, but with a little training, this can improve. Sometimes he also will whine initially when he is left alone, but he settles down after a short time. Kippie gets along well with dogs and people. He is house-, crate- and leash trained, but does pull while on the leash because he is so eager to smell everything. His favorite pastime is playing with his ball, chewing on his bones and hanging with his family.Unfortunately, Kippie is heartworm positive so he needs to be with a family on the Mississippi Gulf Coast so he can continue treatment with the same vet. Also, he will have to remain quiet during his treatment and for a few months afterwards. Kippie is neutered, up to date on vaccinations and microchipped. His adoption fee is $175. Available through Tired Dog Rescue, Gulfport, MS. If you would love to give this wonderful boy a forever home, please apply at tireddogrescue.org

animal.description:
Meet this handsome fella named Buddy! He came into the shelter January 15, 2021 when his owner could no longer keep him. He is 2 and a half years old, current on shots, now neutered, and a big handsome fella! He’s strong and weighs almost 90 pounds so he needs a handler understands his strength and size. He is a love of a pup and misses his home life setting. Maybe you have the most amazing FOREVER home for Buddy?! Visit with him today and adopt him into your heart and home!
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5 and Sat. 10-4. Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.
animal.name: Buddy

animal.description:
This is Brandi. Brandi is 1 of the 8 puppies we rescued from a woman’s home in Orangeburg, SC. The momma dog made a nest inside of the insulation underneath the woman’s home, and the lady wanted them out. 

While we were getting the puppies to safety, the momma dog ran away. After searching for the momma dog for 2 hours in the cold rain, we came up empty. 

Without the momma dog around, we, ourselves, have had to become the “mom”!! This means buying puppy milk replacement, cleaning, bathing, and bottle feeding all 8 puppies!!

Brandi is now old enough to find her forever home!! Brandi is great with other dogs, loves all people, and loves to receive cuddles and attention anytime and anywhere!!

Please consider Brandi when you are looking for your next family member and companion!

Meet this handsome fella named Hercules! His owner surrendered him to another shelter and we offered to help him since we had some space. He came into our shelter January 19, 2021 and is now current on shots, and awaiting his chance at a happily ever after. Hercules is 4 years old and a happy boy full of happiness and love to share. He’s a bundle of energy and excitement and would love a home with a big fenced in yard to run around in BUT he loves his people and wants to soak up all the TLC and affection one has to give too. A real sweetheart for sure!! Might you have the most amazing loving FOREVER home for this charming 64 pound hunk of love?! Visit with him today! 
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5 and Sat. 10-4. Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.

animal.description:
Hi guys, I’m Moira a 43 lbs, 1 year old female terrier mix.  I made my way up to Wisconsin from Oklahoma to find my forever home.  One thing I can say is I’m not  a fan of this cold.  I’m working on my potty training (I will get there soon) but as soon as I go outside, I will quick do my business because my butt wants to get back into the house where it’s nice and warm.  Speaking of my butt, it NEVER stops wiggling.  NEVER!  My foster mom says I have to be one of the happiest dogs she has met and I love meeting new people.  When someone new comes to the house, I’m the first one to greet them at the door like they are my long lost friend.  I also very much enjoy the 3 resident dogs that live here with me.  We play a lot!  There also is a resident cat here that I’m a little interested in...I think she wants to be my friend but sometimes I get a little to excited when I see her that I think she wants me to chase her.  I guess she doesn’t like that to much.  I’m also starting to learn that my crate isn’t to bad, I will cry some at the beginning and then I will just give up and lay down.  
I haven’t been around any small children yet.  My foster mom thinks I would do best with ones that were a little older.  I give so many kisses because I love kisses but sometimes those kisses will turn into nibbles.  I just love humans so much that I get a little excited and forget that I need to be gentle.  I do listen when I’m reminded though.
I would love a family that will give my lots of attention and play fun games with.  I can be a little antsy when no one is paying attention to me and I will pace back and fourth.

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 

Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you, please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

animal.description:
Yotey was found with her 2 pups stranded way out in the desert...they were starving, dirty, and full of worms. Luckily, some good samaritans spotted them and contacted us. They are all safe now and looking for their forever homes. She appears to be about 2-3 years old and a German Shepherd/Husky mix. We call her Yotey because she looked like a coyote out there in the desert, but she is an extremely sweet dog. She had a companion who has already been adopted so we think she would do best in a home where she would have another dog to pal around with. She is playful yet calm and just an all around fantastic dog! 

Please do NOT call or email. The first step in the process is for you to completely fill out the adoption application in the link below. If your application is incomplete, we will move on to the next one. 

Due to Covid-19 we are conducting the home checks virtually. So once you have submitted your application, please take photos and/or video of your home, front and back yards, fencing, gates, other pets in your home, where this pet would be sleeping, etc. Then compose an email, attach the photos, and in the subject line of the email please put "Your Full Name (as it appears on the application you submitted) - the name of the pup you applied for". This will help us to match your email to your application in our software. Send the email to infosatg@gmail.com and an adoption counselor will review them and contact you if you have met these conditions. ;)

Please understand that we are all unpaid volunteers with our own families, pets, and jobs to attend to it is just not possible to respond to every single person all the time. We do the best we can and appreciate your understanding. (Tip: The more thorough you are in answering the questions on our application and in your "virtual home tour", the more likely it is that you will be contacted. :)

Apply to adopt Yotey at: 
https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/SATG-A-129

animal.description:
Don't miss out on Scrappy by emailing us to see if he is still available.??
Check the Photo Gallery on our website and see if they are marked PENDING OR ADOPTED.
APPLY if interested so you can be considered.
When he is adopted or pending, we put it on the gallery photo of our home page.
PLEASE check our website Daily for any updates.  www.wowdogrescue.org
*Our page is updated daily. Please go to www.wowdogrescue.org for any updates.

Scrappy is a little boy with a lot of curiosity, and high energy.
He was a stray.
We think he is around 1.5 yrs old and weighs in around 9 lbs.
Perhaps a Terrier/chihuahua mix.
He has learned to walk on a leash and needs the exercise. He knows what the
harness is and will stand so you can put it on him.

Scrappy's self confidence is low and he is afraid of fast movements and loud sounds.He is not a candidate for car rides, as they make him
sick to his stomach.
He likes and needs a lot of positive reinforcement.
He is very gentle even when he is afraid he will not growl or try to bite. (He just crouches down).

He LOVES to cuddle on the couch but on his terms.
His preference for a new owner would be a woman.
Scrappy is crate trained, house breaking is a on-going challenge for him but has greatly improved.
(Perhaps once his neuter is done this will improve).

He is great with other dogs, and would benefit from another dog in the home, but he has adjusted well.
He loves soft chew toys and his blanket.
He is not foods aggression and has put on some needed weight.
The fosters feed him 2 times a day but would most likely be fine free feeding.

He will Be neutered on 1/22/21, and also be microchipped, Rabies shot, and has already had his DHPP and Bordetella shot.

Scrappy's adoption fee is $250.00

We are NOT Petfinder,
We are not Adoptapet,
OR
Rescue me.

Our application is on OUR website:  www.wowdogrescue.org

**PLEASE do not call to see if he is "still" available.
His Gallery photo on our website will be updated daily and will state his status.
IF we have chosen someone, he will be marked "Pending".
IF he has been adopted, he will be marked "Adopted".

***Tired of not finding, or not being chosen for the dog of your dream??
Consider Fostering with us...Our Fosters have 1st chance at adopting the dog they foster, while we pay for everything.
Its a win win for both! YOU get to see if this is a good match for your family, while the dog is being loved in your home...

Pumpkin is the sweetest girl once she warms up! She follows her foster mom around the house and likes to sit with her head on her lap. She walks really well on the leash but sometimes gets scared and needs some encouragement. Overall, she is a very good girl looking for a patient and loving family to help her come out of her shell!

Pumpkin is full of love! She is looking for a forever home where she can get lots of belly rubs and can give all the kisses!

Interested in adding Pumpkin to your family? Apply online today!

animal.description: Hi! My name is Star Rose! I was rescued by an animal shelter in South Carolina before arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. animal.description: Spade is a very sweet boy who is terribly traumatized. We don't know what he's been though, but we know it must have been horrible. Spade wants very badly to trust, but it will take a very special person and a lot of TLC for him to become the dog he's meant to be. We want to be very transparent about the fact that he is extremely shut down. Spade will need someone extremely patient and understanding while he decompresses and settles into a home. It may take months before he begins to come out of his shell and become comfortable with people - the timeline is different for every dog. We are hoping to find an adopter experienced in socializing fearful dogs. Please understand that Spade's journey will not be an easy one and will require a significant commitment. Spade is 40lbs and estimated to be 12yrs old. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines and microchipped. His adoption fee is donation based. Please go to www.angelsretreat.org to apply.
